Sentencas: The perovskite-type oxides were synthesized in the series of Ln(1-x)Sr(x)CoO(3) (Ln = Sm, Dy).
Titulo: Ln(1-x)Sr(x)CoO(3) (Ln=Sm, Dy) for the electrode of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The formation of solid solutions in Dy1-xSrxCoO3 was limited, compared with that in Sm1-xSrxCoO3.
Titulo: Ln(1-x)Sr(x)CoO(3) (Ln=Sm, Dy) for the electrode of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrical conductivities of the sintered samples were measured as a function of x in the temperature range 30 to 1000 degrees C.
Titulo: Ln(1-x)Sr(x)CoO(3) (Ln=Sm, Dy) for the electrode of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The highest conductivity of around 500 Slcm at 1000 degrees C was found in Sm0.7Sr0.3CoO3.
Titulo: Ln(1-x)Sr(x)CoO(3) (Ln=Sm, Dy) for the electrode of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The reactivity of all the samples with YSZ was examined at 800-1000 degrees C for 96 h. The Sr-doped perovskite oxides were more reactive with YSZ and produced SrZrO3 at 900 degrees C after 96 h. However, no reaction product between SmCoO3 and YSZ was observed at 1000 degrees C for 96 h.
Titulo: Ln(1-x)Sr(x)CoO(3) (Ln=Sm, Dy) for the electrode of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The cathodic polarization of the oxide electrodes, sputtered on yttria stabilized zirconia (YSZ), was studied at 800-1000 degrees C in air.
Titulo: Ln(1-x)Sr(x)CoO(3) (Ln=Sm, Dy) for the electrode of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: SmCoO, shows no degradation of the electrode performance at higher temperatures.
Titulo: Ln(1-x)Sr(x)CoO(3) (Ln=Sm, Dy) for the electrode of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The thermal expansion measurements on the sintered samples were carried out from room temperature to 1000 degrees C. Large thermal expansion coefficients were found in these samples.
Titulo: Ln(1-x)Sr(x)CoO(3) (Ln=Sm, Dy) for the electrode of solid oxide fuel cells
